      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction; Jan 10 article about secure telephone in New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg's home misquoted him</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Because of an editing error, an article yesterday about a secure telephone that Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg uses in his Manhattan town house rendered incorrectly a quotation from him. The mayor said he had occasionally received calls on the secure line asking ''did I want to subscribe to a particular magazine, buy an insurance policy or some other such ridiculous thing.'' He did not say the callers asked ''did I want to subscribe to a ridiculous magazine, buy an insurance policy or some other such particular thing.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
